      "content": "(Introduction)",
      "table": `<table>\n  <tr>\n    <th>Overview of the Audit Unit, its functional/geographical jurisdiction</th>\n    <th>The Engineer-in Chief (R&B), NH & Buildings is responsible for the execution of the buildings, National Highway and CRF works in the State and the quality control of the works. He is also responsible for the according sanction to the estimate/revised estimate.\nFor buildings work, he is assisted by one Dy. Chief Engineer of the rank of Superintending Engineer and one Executive Engineer in his office. For National Highways and CRF work also, he is assisted by one Dy. Chief Engineer and one Executive Engineer. \nIn addition, there are two circle offices at Hyderabad   under his control for implementation of building works and three circle offices at Hyderabad, Warangal and Nizamabad for implementation of National Highways work at the field/sites.</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Budget and Financial Performance of the Unit</td>\n    <td>This Office issues Technical Sanction for the works above three crore. Pay and allowances and other office expenses/contingent of this Office are drawn by Chief Engineer (R&B) Admin., & QC, Errum Manzil Hyderabad. Hence, no expenditure is met from this Office.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Relative significance of the Unit in the overall hierarchy of the Department in pursuit of Organizational goals</td>\n    <td>Engineer-in Chief (R&B), NH, & Buildings is responsible for the sanction of estimates/deviations and revised estimates and supervising the execution of the buildings, National Highway and CRF under his jurisdiction and quality control of works.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Scope of Audit, the sampling procedure followed, and the sample audited. (Includes the implementing unit, the subject matter(s) selected and the sources of criteria that have been adopted to evaluate the selected subject matter)</td>\n    <td>The Accounts of the Office were last audited in November 2020.   During the present Audit, the accounts of the office, for the period from the last Audit to August 2023 were generally examined. In the current audit, the records of four unique building works viz  new Secretariat work, command control center work, Telangana Martyrs Memorial work and erection of Dr. BR Ambedkar Statue were verified. Audit also test checked three National Highway works and new three Telangana Institute of Medical Sciences (TIMS) works and two IDOCs works.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Whether the Audit has been conducted in accordance with the applicable Auditing Standards of CAG (specify)</td>\n    <td>Yes</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>`
