      "title": "Reference Number: OBS-1070128",
      "content": "#### II: UNDUE BENEFIT TO CONTRACTOR IN REFILLING WORK\n\nThe work “the construction of new Secretariat for the State of Telangana in the premises of old secretariat complex” was technically sanctioned (September 2020) for ₹617.00 crore. On call of tenders, the work was awarded (November 2020) to M/s Sharpoorji Pallonji and Company Pvt Ltd, for an agreement value of ₹514.75 crore at 4.02 percent excess over the ECV for completion in 12 months. Scrutiny of the records revealed the following:\n\n#### Undue benefit to contractor in refilling work-₹0.67 crore\n\nAgreement conditions (clause 37 and clause 39) stipulate that the contractor is to be paid for the quantity of the work done at the estimate rate in the bill of quantity of the work done for each item plus or minus tender percentage. The payment rates for supplemental items which are not covered in the agreement are only to be regulated according to the conditions stipulated in the agreement.\n\nThe scope of the work provides for refilling with available excavated earth in low lying areas and in trenches, sides of foundations and basement etc. The sanctioned rate for refilling with available excavated soil was ₹52 per cum (Sl.No.15 of the original estimate) and the corresponding rate with conveyance of material within 1 km was ₹ 87 per cum (Sl. No. 6 of the original estimate). The rates were correctly arrived at in the original estimate by taking the Standard data (BLD-CSTN-2-9). The contractor was also made aware of the sanctioned rates of refilling items of works in the pre-bid meeting. However, later the Department chose to revise the rate at ₹ 427 per cum for refilling with available excavated earth from the dump yard with 1 km by adding some other elements of compaction charges etc discarding the Standard Data in the deviation statement-I (March 2022). This resulted in undue benefit of ₹ 0.67 crore to the contractor.\n\n\n\nOn this being pointed out, the Department replied that work items (Sl. No. 6 and 15) of the original estimate pertain to the filling/refilling of useful available earth by manual means. As no machinery component was taken into consideration in the original estimate, new data was prepared considering loading charges, conveyances, and compaction charges.\n\nThe reply is not correct as the building data standard available for refilling with useful excavated earth is common for all works. It is nowhere mentioned that data is for manual means. According to specifications 309 and 310 of APDSS, filling should be done in layers not exceeding 150 mm, each layer being watered and compacted before the succeeding layer is laid. Building standard data approved by the Government was based on the consideration of these specifications. These specifications are also mentioned in the description of the item of work. As stated above, the contractor was also already made aware of the sanctioned rates of this item in the pre-bid meeting. Hence, the revising of the rates on unsubstantiated grounds was incorrect and excess payment should be recovered under intimation to audit.\n\n#### Undue benefit to contractor in carting of the material\n\nThe general method followed for arriving at the rate for carting of excavated soil or rock is to apply the conveyance rate provided in the Schedule of Rates (SoR) according to the extent of lead (conveyance) required. Loading and unloading charges of the carted material are not payable for conveyance by mechanical means for disposal of excavated material unless specified as per the revised Standard Data (Building). The method was correctly applied in the original estimate while arriving at the rate for earth work in excavation including carting of excavated material for depositing at a place within 1 km distance (Sl.No.1 of the original estimate) also in refilling with excavated material by re-carting (Sl.No.6 of the original estimate) without loading charges and unloading charges. However, deviating from the general method approved in the original estimate, the Department decided to manipulate the data in the internal carting of excavated material within 1 km by including loading and unloading charges. This resulted in undue benefit of ₹44.86 lakh to the contractor.\n\n\n\nOn this being pointed out, Department replied that during construction, the excavated material from all blocks was carted and stacked at the new location ie Northeast corner and a new data was prepared duly considering the loading, unloading and conveyance of excavated material with an initial lead of 1 km by mechanical means.\n\nHowever, the matter of fact is that loading and unloading charges of the carted material are not payable for conveyance by mechanical means for disposal of excavated material unless specified as per the revised Standard Data (Building). Department should not have a fluctuating stand as far as this data/rate analysis of internal carting/disposal of excavated earth/rock is concerned. The technical sanctioning authority should not entertain the revision of rates by deviating from the Standard Data approved by the Government. In case of a necessary amendment to the Standard Data, the matter may be placed before the Board of Chief Engineers (BoCE) for consideration of amendment. Interestingly, the same Technical Sanctioning Authority approved the rates of carting/disposal of earth/rock without loading and unloading in the works of Telangana Martyrs Memorial.",
      "table": "<table>\n  <tr>\n    <th>Item</th>\n    <th>Quantity (cum)</th>\n    <th>Original estimate rate (₹ per cum)</th>\n    <th>Revised rate (₹ per cum)</th>\n    <th>Difference (₹ per cum)</th>\n    <th>Undue benefit (₹)</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Filling with useful available excavated earth from dumpyard with        1 km</td>\n    <td>18,991.64</td>\n    <td>87</td>\n    <td>427</td>\n    <td>340</td>\n    <td>6457157.60</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td colspan=\"5\">Add TP at 4.02%</td>\n    <td>259577.74</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td colspan=\"5\">Total</td>\n    <td>6716735.34</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n<table>\n  <tr>\n    <th>Item</th>\n    <th>Quantity (cum)</th>\n    <th>Rate to be taken (₹/cum)</th>\n    <th>Rate taken by the Department (₹/cum)</th>\n    <th>Difference (₹/cum)</th>\n    <th>Amount (₹)</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Internal carting of excavated soil</td>\n    <td>19009.3</td>\n    <td>35.3</td>\n    <td>109</td>\n    <td>73.7</td>\n    <td>1400985.41</td>\n``````markdown\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Internal carting of excavated rock</td>\n    <td>22538.3</td>\n    <td>33.8</td>\n    <td>163</td>\n    <td>129.2</td>\n    <td>2911948.36</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td></td>\n    <td></td>\n    <td></td>\n    <td></td>\n    <td></td>\n    <td>4312933.77</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td colspan=\"5\">Add TP at 4.02 percent</td>\n    <td>173379.94</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td colspan=\"5\">Total</td>\n    <td>4486313.71</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>"
