      "id": "7140a690-5952-4cb2-b612-bb6a64896f48",
      "label": "Reference",
      "title": "Reference Number: OBS-1077903",
      "content": "#### III. FINALISATION OF RATE OF MACHINE CUTTING CHARGES OF RED/BEIGE SANDSTONE ON POSSIBLE FABRICATED QUOTATION\n\nThe work “Erection of 125 feet tall statue of Dr. B.R. Ambedkar at Hillock area of NTR garden premises, Hyderabad was technically sanctioned (January 2021) for ₹146.50 crore. On call of tenders, the work was awarded (June 2021) to M/s KPC Projects limited, Hyderabad for an agreement value of ₹104.19 crore at 3.94 percent excess over the estimated contract value. The work was stipulated to be completed in 12 months.\n\nIn the original estimate an amount of ₹20 core was provided for construction of the Main building for the Project. However, subsequently the cost of the building was increased to ₹31.56 crore which was more than 50 percent of the original amount. One of the main reasons for the increase in cost was the revision of rates for sandstone works. Scrutiny of the records revealed that, rate provided for red sandstone work in the estimate was ₹50941 per cum. The rate was however revised at ₹ 2,07,901.98 per cum (August 2023) by adopting a revised data. The revised data was also applied for other similar stonework viz beige sandstone for columns and parapet walls. The main factor for increasing the cost of item of the work was the inclusion of the cutting charges of the stone at ₹970 per sft (quotation rate) and its consequential conversion of the rate at ₹143704 per cum (₹970 per sft/0.00675) in the revised rate. Scrutiny revealed that rate of the cutting charge at ₹970 per sft was approved based on the quotations received from the three firms/suppliers viz (i) RBS Construction, Hyderabad (ii) GOSTONEART, Hindaun city, Rajasthan (iii) Shivansh stone, Hindaun City, Hyderabad. However, none of the suppliers mentioned the dates of the quotation and validity period of the rates in the quotation letters. The Audit also observed that the description of work and letter format and font size of letters in the quotation letters furnished by suppliers were one and same, indicating the possible fabrication of the quotation letters. Further, one of the quotations mentioned the unit of rate in terms of cubic metre while another two in square feet and comparative statement was prepared assuming all units in square feet.\n\nOn this being pointed out, the Department replied that after the agreement was concluded, certain changes such as locating the statue on Hillock and direction of statue were finalized after deliberations with Higher Authorities in Government and the work was grounded thereafter on 02.09.2021. And also submitted that a decision was taken to get the project completed on war footing and inaugurate it to match the birth anniversary of Dr. B.R Ambedkar. As such, the schedules of all activities were squeezed and the formalities of addressing written enquiry of quotation could not be placed. Instead, the vendors were called to the work site and quotations were obtained at site.\n\nThe reply of the Department might not be factually correct as two suppliers were from Rajasthan State and obtained the quotation from them at work site in the absence of the documentary evidence. As stated above, one supplier submitted the rate of CNC cutting in terms of cubic metre whereas the other two in square feet. However, there should not be this sort of contradictory quotation in terms of units of rates in case a clear discussion happened with suppliers either at site or through mail/any other correspondence. Even, it was not clear to Audit how Department decided to take the rate in terms of square feet when written enquiry was not placed to the suppliers.\n\nAs regards the finalization of rate of the sandstone work, the Department submitted that the Consultant furnished the detailed drawing of sandstone in January 2023 with full details of stone carving. As the base rate of sandstone (Ashlar Masonry) was already available in sanction estimate, it was adopted as the base rate to which transport charge was added. For the carving cost, CPWD did not have any rate. Hence, market quotations were obtained which were worked out on the complexity of carving design on square feet bases with CNC Technology. On the consequential conversion of the rate of CNC cutting in terms of cubic metre at ₹143704 per cum from the quotation rate of ₹970 per sft, Department clarified that the size of the sand stone block was 0.00675 cum (0.30x0.30x0.075) and for stone block size of 0.00675 cum, the rate of cutting was ₹970 per sft.\n\nHowever, the fact is that there is no logic to assume that in stone block size of 0.00675 cum, there will be cutting area of 1 square feet without mentioning any depth of cutting in the quotation. Audit therefore suggests the Department to review the revised rate judiciously to avoid the huge cost implication.",
