      "id": "968ee789-d37f-4efd-888a-ef148448c623",
      "label": "Reference",
      "title": "Reference Number: OBS-1077832",
      "content": "#### IV. REVISION OF RATES IN FLOORING WORKS IN VIOLATION OF THE AGREEMENT CONDITIONS\n\nThe work “construction of new secretariat for the State of Telangana in the premises of old secretariat complex” was technically sanctioned (September 2020) for ₹617.00 crore. On call of tenders, the work was awarded (November 2020) to M/s Sharpoorji Pallonji and Company Pvt Ltd KPC Projects limited, for an agreement value of ₹514.75 crore at 4.02 percent excess over the ECV for completion in 12 months.\n\nAs per tender conditions/Agreement conditions (Clause 8 bid offer), the tenderers should work out his own rates keeping in view of the work, site conditions and quote his overall percentage with which he intends to execute the work. Agreement conditions (clauses 37 and 39) stipulate that the contractor is to be paid for the quantity of the work done at the estimate rate in the bill of quantity of the work done for each item plus or minus tender percentage. The payment rates for supplemental items which are not covered in the agreement are only to be regulated according to the conditions stipulated in the agreement.\n\nHowever, scrutiny of the records revealed that the rate of the item of work “flooring with high polished granite 16-18mm thick of premium colour (other than black) etc in the ground floor” which was already covered by the agreement at the estimated rate of ₹4796 per sqm, was revised in deviation statement-III (October 2022) at ₹5802.00 per sqm by restructuring the Standard data incorporating (i) additional labour charges for fixing of inlay works and power saw-hand operated hire charges etc and (ii) higher granite material factor of 11.50 sqm in lieu of 10.50 sqm in the Standard data. Standard data (BLD-CSTN-9-7) for flooring with high polished granite does not include these additional cost elements in the Data itself. This maneuvering of data by the Department in violation of the tender/agreement conditions resulted in undue benefit of ₹2.26 crore to the contractor.\n\n\n\nOn this being pointed out, the Department replied that in the original estimate, the above item of work was exclusive of inlay works. As per the flooring sample approved by Hon’ble CM, the architect proposed the flooring with high polished granite including inlay works depicting the design pattern other than the agreement specification and issued drawings accordingly. Hence, the rate analysis was prepared considering the labour and machinery charges for inlay works and same was approved in deviation statement.\n\nHowever, the fact remains that there was no agreement condition which can entertain any revision of agreement items. In addition, the inclusion of charges of inlay works and other additional cost elements has no references of any standard data under which Audit can verify the correctness of data of inlay works arrived by the Department. In the similar flooring item in the work of erection of Dr.BR Ambedkar statue, Department had chosen to revise the rate by a different method with the addition of machine cutting charges and taking of material granite factor of 11 sqm in lieu of 10.50 sqm provided in the standard data. Audit opines that it is irregular on the part of Technical Sanctioning Authority/Agreement Concluding Authority to accept the revision of rates in any method agreeable to the contractors, without any enabling agreement conditions or any amendments to the Standard Data.",
