      "title": "Reference Number: OBS-1077878",
      "content": "#### V. COST IMPLICATION DUE TO REVISION OF RATES IN PROVIDING CLADDING WITH HIGH POLISHED GRANITE IN THE DEVIATION STATEMENT-III\n\nThe work “the construction of new secretariat for the State of Telangana in the premises of old secretariat complex” was technically sanctioned (September 2020) for ₹617.00 crore. On call of tenders, the work was awarded (November 2020) to M/s Sharpoorji Pallonji and Company Pvt Ltd KPC Projects limited, for an agreement value of ₹514.75 crore at 4.02 percent excess over the ECV for completion in 12 months.\n\nAs per tender conditions/Agreement conditions (Clause 8 bid offer), the tenderers should work out his own rates keeping in view of the work, site conditions and quote his overall percentage with which he intends to execute the work. Agreement conditions (clause 37) stipulate that the contractor is to be paid for the quantity of the work done at the estimate rate in the bill of quantity of the work done for each item plus or minus tender percentage. The payment rates for supplemental items which are not covered in the agreement are only to be regulated according to the conditions stipulated in the agreement. However, scrutiny of the deviation statement-III revealed that Department kept on revising the rates of flooring, cladding with high polished granite etc on the ground that approved specification for this item differs from the item considered in the technical sanction.\n\nIn the item of the work “ providing cladding with 16 to 18 mm thick High Polished Granite up to 8'-00 (2.43 M) of premium colours (other than black) which was originally sanctioned at ₹4,526 /sqm (lower ground floor rate) ”, Department revised the rate of this agreement item at ₹7,310/sqm by adding the cost of groove of 8mm at the factor of 218.68 Rft and power saw cutter-hand operated hire charges at the factor of 16 hrs. As these cost elements are not provided in the Standard data BLD-CSTN-9-19, inclusion of the same was irregular in the absence of any enabling agreement conditions for revision of agreement items and entailed huge undue benefit ₹ 4.10 crore to the contractor as shown below:\n\n\n\n\n\nOn this being pointed out, the Department replied that in the original estimate, the rate of the item of the cladding with high polished granite was exclusive of groove making charges. During the execution, the Architect submitted the drawings duly providing grooves to cladding with high polished granite. Accordingly, after several mockup at site, grooves were executed. As there was no approved data for such type of specialized works, observed data was worked out and same was approved in the deviation statement.\n\nHowever, the fact remains that there was no agreement condition which can entertain any revision of agreement items. In addition, the inclusion of groove making charges and other additional cost elements has no references of any standard data under which Audit can verify the correctness of data of groove charges cooked by the Department. The acceptance of the revision of rates in any method agreeable to the contractors, without any agreement conditions or any other amendments to the Standard data by the Technical Sanctioning Authority/Agreement Concluding Authority is irregular.",
      "table": "<table>\n  <tr>\n    <th>Description of work</th>\n    <th>Quantity (sqm)</th>\n    <th>Rate as per original estimate (₹/sqm)</th>\n    <th>Revised rate (₹/sqm)</th>\n    <th>Difference (₹/sqm)</th>\n    <th colspan=\"2\">Amount(₹)</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Providing cladding with 16 to 18 mm thick High Polished Granite up to 8'-00 (2.43 M) of premium  colours (other than black)  (APSS No.701 & 707)</td>\n    <td></td>\n    <td></td>\n    <td></td>\n    <td></td>\n    <td colspan=\"2\"></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Lower Ground Level (F1)</td>\n    <td>2,047.86</td>\n    <td>4,526</td>\n    <td>7,310</td>\n    <td>2,784</td>\n```    <td colspan=\"2\">5701242.24</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Ground Floor (F2)</td>\n    <td>2,175.92</td>\n    <td>4,588</td>\n    <td>7,371</td>\n    <td>2,783</td>\n    <td colspan=\"2\">6055585.36</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>1st Floor (F3)</td>\n    <td>2,152.82</td>\n    <td>4,649</td>\n    <td>7,433</td>\n    <td>2,784</td>\n    <td colspan=\"2\">5993450.88</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>2nd Floor (F4)</td>\n    <td>2,214.32</td>\n    <td>4,711</td>\n    <td>7,494</td>\n    <td>2,783</td>\n    <td colspan=\"2\">6162452.56</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>3rd Floor (F5)</td>\n    <td>2,214.32</td>\n    <td>4,772</td>\n    <td>7,556</td>\n    <td>2,784</td>\n    <td colspan=\"2\">6164666.88</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>4th Floor (F6)</td>\n    <td>2,214.32</td>\n    <td>4,834</td>\n    <td>7,617</td>\n    <td>2,783</td>\n    <td colspan=\"2\">6162452.56</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>5th Floor (F7)</td>\n    <td>2,214.32</td>\n    <td>4,895</td>\n    <td>7,679</td>\n    <td>2,784</td>\n    <td colspan=\"2\">6164666.88</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td></td>\n    <td></td>\n    <td></td>\n    <td></td>\n    <td></td>\n    <td colspan=\"2\">42404517.36</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td colspan=\"6\">Add TP at 4.02%</td>\n    <td colspan=\"2\">1704661.60</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td colspan=\"6\">Total</td>\n    <td colspan=\"2\">44109178.96</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>"
