      "id": "4b54d080-79ea-42f9-b740-8fc37be08f86",
      "label": "Reference",
      "title": "Reference Number: OBS-1077935",
      "content": "#### XIII. INFLATION OF ESTIMATE DUE TO INCORRECT ADOPTION OF RATE OF WATER CHARGES AND OVERHEAD CHARGE -₹ 2.67 CRORE\n\nThe work “Widening to two lane with paved shoulders from Km 0/000 to Km 79/300 of Kalwakurthy – Kollapur section NH – 167 in the State of Telangana  was entrusted ( April 2023) to M/s RKIPL-KMV(JV) under EPC system of contract for an agreement amount of ₹ 401.11 crore. The work was scheduled for completion in 24 months from the date of agreement.\n\nOn Scrutiny of rate analysis of the  item  work “Construction of granular sub-base (GSB)”,  it was observed that Department adopted the rate of water tanker hire charges at ₹ 1113.30 per hour incorrectly instead of ₹699 per hour as provided in SoR. It  also  took the overhead charges at 5 percent  in lieu of  3 percent applicable for road works.  Due to adoption of incorrect charges/rate, unit  rate of the above item of work  was worked out  at ₹2587.00 per cum instead of ₹ 2533.00 per cum (Annexure-5). Consequent inflation of estimate of  ₹0.98 crore is shown below.\n\n.\n\n\n\nSimilarly, in the rate analysis for  laying of wet mix macadam (WMM) also, Department committed same mistake resulting in adoption of rates higher by ₹68.00 per cum    (Annexure-6).\n\nThis resulted in undue benefit to the contractor to the extent of ₹1.69 crore as shown below.\n\n\n\nThus, due to the adoption of higher rates in the above two items of work, the Department inflated the estimate by ₹ 2.67 crore to the contractor.\n\nOn this being pointed out, the Department replied that as per the PMC contract agreement Clause 7.1.1, the Consultant is  responsible for accuracy of the data collected by him directly or procured from other agencies/authorities, the designs, drawings, estimates and all other details prepared by him as part of these services. The Department stated that as per the explanation submitted by the consultant, they adopted the rates as per practical and realistic conditions. It was submitted that rate of vibratory roller was adopted in lieu of the rate of smooth wheeled roller and 5% over head charges was adopted as per general engineering practice.\n\nHowever, the fact remains that the project cost was inflated on account of the incorrect inclusion of machinery rate and higher overhead charges. The Department should take the rate as provided in SoR and should give a better picture of the project cost to the Government while submitting the project proposal so that project cost sanctioned by the Government was not inflated.",
