      "id": "b1f3d616-2d5e-44e4-b5b3-d0b46522449d",
      "label": "Reference",
      "title": "Reference Number: OBS-1077961",
      "content": "#### XIV. NON-DEDUCTION OF EMBEDDED TAX\n\nAfter introduction of Goods and Services Tax (GST) (July 2017), the Works Contracts were being subjected to GST at the rate of 12 per cent/18 per cent. Thus, to avoid GST on the Taxes already included in the cost of works, the Government of Telangana issued (July 2018) orders vide GO Ms.No.67 of I&CAD (Reforms) Department, dated 04 July 2018  that in respect of the works done after 01 July 2017, the taxes already embedded in the rates/materials under the existing contracts should be deducted and to the net value of work so arrived at, GST at the rates applicable from time to time should be added while making payments to contractors.\n\nIn the work “Construction of Hyderabad City Police Commissionerate Head Quarters and Integrated Command & Control Centre at Banjara Hills, Rd No 12, Hyderabad” Department worked out the Embedded Tax to be deducted from the material cost and arrived at ₹25,22,74,603. However, on test check revealed that Department left out items of main building work (approx. cost ₹9.25 crore) from the ambit of the Embedded Tax deduction criteria and reasons for the same were not on record and made available to Audit.  The non consideration of Embedded Tax was an undue benefit to the contractor.\n\n\n\nOn this being pointed out, the Department replied that there was no clarity on the taxes embedded on the items considered, whose rates were derived from the Delhi Schedule of Rates. However, the Embedded Taxes for these items would be deducted as per the Embedded Taxes included for the similar SoR items.\n\nThe fact of the deduction of Embedded Tax may be furnished to Audit along with the calculation sheet for verification.",
