      "id": "734f2c18-2cc1-4088-8b75-1aa4d33a20c3",
      "label": "Reference",
      "title": "Reference Number: OBS-1077916",
      "content": "#### XVI. INFLATION OF ESTIMATE DUE TO ADOPTION OF INCORRECT RATE OF MACHINERY HIRE CHARGE, LABOUR CHARGE AND OVERHEAD CHARGE- ₹ 25.58 LAKH\n\nThe work “Widening to two lane with paved shoulders from Km 0/000 to Km 79/300 of Kalwakurthy – Kollapur section NH – 167 in the State of Telangana was entrusted ( April 2023) to M/s RKIPL-KMV(JV) under EPC system of contract for an agreement amount of ₹ 401.11 crore. The work was scheduled for completion in 24 months from the date of agreement.\n\nOn Scrutiny of rate analysis of the item work “Providing and applying primer coat with bitumen emulsion on prepared surface of granular base etc.,” Audit observed that the Department adopted incorrect rates of mate (labourer) and water tanker charges and  also  the Overhead Charges at 5% instead of 3% applicable for road works.  Due to this, the unit rate was taken at ₹ 34 per sqm instead of ₹33 per sqm (Annexure 7) and consequent inflation of estimate of ₹8.56 lakh as detailed below.\n\n\n\nSimilarly, on scrutiny of the item of the work “Providing tack coat 0.20 to 0.25 kg per sqm on prepared bituminous surface and 0.25 to 0.30 kg per sqm on prepared granular surface” the rate of machinery and Overhead charges were incorrectly computed (Annexure-8). This resulted in inflation of estimate to the extent of ₹ 17.02 lakh as shown below.\n\n\n\nOn this being pointed out, the Department replied that as per the PMC contract agreement Clause 7.1.1, the Consultant is responsible for accuracy of the data collected by him directly or procured from other Agencies/Authorities, the designs, drawings, estimates and all other details prepared by him as part of these services. The Department stated that as per the explanation submitted by the Consultant, they adopted the rates as per practical and realistic conditions. And also submitted that rate of vibratory roller was adopted in lieu of the rate of smooth wheeled roller, and 5% Overhead Charges was adopted as per general engineering practice.\n\nHowever, the fact remains that the project cost was inflated on account of the incorrect inclusion of machinery rate and higher Overhead Charges. The Department should take the rate as provided in SoR and should give a better picture of the Project cost to the Government while submitting the project proposal so that Project cost sanctioned by the Government was not inflated.",
